Charles C. Spotswood, appellant, v. William F. Jackson, appellee.Gen. No. 26,744.Action to recover a commission for the sale of real estate. Judgment for defendant on motion reversed for new trial. Judgment for defendant on second trial. Appeal from the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Hosea W. Wells, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1921.Affirmed.

Barnes, J., took no part in the decision of this ease.

Opinion filed March 21, 1922.Cavender & Kaiser and A. D. Ranstead, for appellant. Ivor Jeffreys, for appellee; David H. Jackson, of counsel. Mr. Justice Morrill

delivered the opinion of the court.
